#N Buckaroo
#C A period-30 oscillating glider reflector. Redirects a glider stream
#C 90 degrees. Based on a queen bee shuttle stabilized by an eater.
#C In digital logic, reflectors act as wire bends — they change the
#C direction of a signal without losing it.
#C Discovered by David Buckingham in the 1970s.
#C Colour-preserving. Feed it a glider stream timed to period-30.
x = 25, y = 19, rule = B3/S23
